#STEP 1 — Install PostgreSQL Driver

Inside your venv:

pip uninstall pymysql
pip install psycopg2-binary


#STEP 8 — CLEAN MIGRATIONS (IMPORTANT)

Since you’re switching DB type:

Delete old versions:
rm -rf migrations/versions/*

Then:

alembic revision --autogenerate -m "initial_postgresql_schema"
alembic upgrade head

You now have clean PostgreSQL schema.

#CHECK YOUR MODELS FOR MYSQL SPECIFIC CODE

Search your project:

grep -r "mysql" app/
grep -r "CURRENT_TIMESTAMP" app/
grep -r "onupdate" app/

Remove MySQL-specific column configs like:

server_default=text("CURRENT_TIMESTAMP ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP")

Replace with:

from sqlalchemy.sql import func

updated_at = Column(DateTime, onupdate=func.now())


